Model will consider cumulative value and gives result based on that. Hence we need to convert into below format.

Converting one form of number into another form of number is called either standardization or Normalization

Standardization:

Converting the number into another form that produces normal distribution
Note: Revolves around Mean (Average)
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
(-2,-1,0,1,2)

Normalization:

Converting the number into another form that produces uniform distribution
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
(0,1,2)

When to use ?

Model that is working based on "Distance Based Algorithm"

When is StandardScaler and when is MinMaxScaler is used?
    When u know the pattern of the data distribution, then go for StandardScaler.
    When u dont know the pattern of the data distribution, then go for MinMaxScaler.

Algorithm or Models that works in Distance Based.
